If you see cracked, missing, or discolored caulk around windows, doors, tubs, or sinks, don’t ignore it. Water sneaks in through those gaps and can cause wood rot, mold, and wasted energy.
Quick DIY check: press gently along the caulk line — if it flakes or pulls away, it’s shot. You can replace small sections with exterior or bathroom-grade silicone caulk, but for a neat, long-lasting job I’ll clean the joint, remove the old caulk, and apply a smooth, weatherproof bead.


